HEADWORD: Chalcid fly
<hw>Chal"cid fly`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From Gr. <grk>chalko`s</grk>
copper; in allusion to its metallic colors.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of a numerous family of hymenopterous insects
(<fam>Chalcidid⟦ae⟧</fam>. Many are gallflies, others are parasitic on
insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chalcidian</ent>⟦br⟧
